<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-564-837  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 564 837.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  Oct 29 1990 n490 p23(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Thriving and surviving. (computer industry during recessions)(Viewpoint) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shaheen, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The computer industry must focus on efficiency, cost reduction andincreased competitiveness to overcome economic slowdowns andincreasing consumer demands.andP;  Companies must develop businessstrategies and link all activities to accomplishing strategicgoals.andP;  Information technologies must contribute to a company'scompetitiveness and profit to be useful.andP;  Large, long-termprojects should be limited in favor of technologies and servicesthat offer quick results and cost advantages.andP;  Year-long projectswith annual paybacks provide the greatest flexibility, althoughlong-term projects are necessary to ensure continued growth.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer IndustryRecessionCost ReductionBusiness PlanningOutlookGuidelines.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>